The Navajo Nation, which includes parts of Utah's San Juan County, announced Friday that it will require all individuals to wear protective masks while in public.
That comes as the Nation announced 85 new COVID-19 cases Friday and three new deaths from the disease.
Fourteen Navajo Nation cases have been confirmed in San Juan County so far.
"Some may not like it, but with the number of positive COVID-19 cases increasing, we have to be proactive in addressing the pandemic.
The Navajo Nation has been disproportionately impacted by the novel coronavirus.